## STRUCTURAL REQUIREMENTS

### JSON Structure MUST Match Template Exactly
```
{
  "category": "[category-name]",
  "totalProducts": [number],
  "products": {
    "1": { [complete product object] },
    "2": { [complete product object] },
    ...
    "5": { [complete product object] }
  }
}
```

### Each Product Object MUST Include (In Order)
1. `id` - string (e.g., "1")
2. `name` - original product name
3. `slug` - URL-friendly version (lowercase, hyphens, no spaces)
4. `price` - current price with $ symbol
5. `originalPrice` - strikethrough price with $ symbol
6. `image` - image file path
7. `imageAlt` - descriptive alt text for accessibility and SEO
8. `description` - short product summary (1-2 sentences)
9. `isNew` - boolean (true/false)
10. `isTrending` - boolean (true/false)
11. `rating` - number (0-5, e.g., 4.8)
12. `reviewCount` - number of reviews (e.g., 150)
13. `stockStatus` - "in-stock" or other status
14. `brand` - manufacturer/brand name
15. `sku` - inventory code (format: "category-id")
16. `cta` - call-to-action text (2-3 words)
17. `affiliateUrl` - Amazon or retailer link
18. `category` - category name
19. `seo` object:
    - `title` - SEO title (50-60 chars, includes main keyword + 2025/year)
    - `description` - Meta description (155-160 chars, compelling, includes long-tail keyword)
    - `keywords` - Array of 8-10 keywords (mix of main, long-tail, topical, user voice searches)
    - `ogImage` - same as image path
20. `fullDescription` object:
    - `html` - Rich HTML description (300-400 words, paragraphs with strong tags, semantic markup)
    - `plainText` - Same content in plain text format (for accessibility)
    - Content must include: product benefits, features, materials, durability, application/usage, target audience, differentiators
    - Write from customer perspective, address pain points, use persuasive language
    - Use power words: "Premium," "Transform," "Salon-quality," "Effortless," etc.
    - Include specific details that competitors might not mention
21. `specifications` object:
    - `packageContents` - What's included
    - `material` - Material composition
    - `finish` - Finish type (Glossy, Matte, etc.)
    - `durability` - How long it lasts (e.g., "7-14 days")
    - `applicationTime` - Time to apply/use
    - `reusable` - Yes/No with frequency if applicable
    - `sizes` - Size options available
    - Add 2-3 more relevant specs unique to the product (e.g., "colorOptions," "waterproof," "hypoallergenic")
22. `relatedProducts` - Array of 5 product IDs that complement this product
23. `relatedCategories` - Array of 3 related category slugs
24. `internalLinks` object with:
    - `blog` - Link to relevant blog post (title, slug, image, excerpt)
    - `inspo` - Link to inspiration/gallery (title, slug, image)
    - `topic` - Link to topic/guide (title, slug, image, description)
25. `faqs` - Array of 4-5 questions with answers
    - Questions should reflect user voice searches and common objections
    - Answers should be 2-3 sentences, helpful and specific
    - Include keywords naturally in questions

